ZOOM.NET ON GNU/DEBIAN LINUX VERSION TESTING/UNSTABLE USING MONO

   YAZ
   Add the following lines to your /etc/apt/sources list 

   deb http://ftp.indexdata.dk/debian indexdata/etch released
   deb-src http://ftp.indexdata.dk/debian indexdata/etch released

   and install YAZ by issuing

   sudo apt-get install yaz libyaz yaz-doc

   Notice: you need YAZ version  2.1.12-1 or newer. The outdated
   standard Debian version 2.1.8-4 will not do the trick.

   MONO NUNIT NANT
   Install from standard Debian packages

   sudo apt-get install mono mono-utils nunit-console nant


   ZOOM.NET
   Fetch zip archive from http://sourceforge.net/projects/zoomdotnet
   and unzip, or fetch CVS version by issuing

   cvs -d:pserver:anonymous@cvs.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/zoomdotnet login
   cvs -z3
         -d:pserver:anonymous@cvs.sourceforge.net:/cvsroot/zoomdotnet 
          co -P Zoom.Net

   cd Zoom.Net

   set environmental variables for MONO to get correct DLL load pathes
   source  mono.sh 

   build and check
   nant
   nant check


